sandshoe
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:the (usually) white canvas, rubber-soled shoe used in tennis and other sports; ?usu. tennis shoe (prob. replaced by <i>sneaker </i>etc
Origin:
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: ca1920 the usual word in Auckland, perhaps because of the number of beaches there. (R. Mason) -- ca1935 (Havelock) commonly used by older people
